Author-Name:    Gardner, Bruce L
Title:   Causes of U.S. Farm Commodity Programs. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 290-310
Issue: 2
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  April 
Abstract:
  This paper i s an attempt to explain variations by commodity in producer
 protection afforded by farm price support programs since the1930s.
 Particularly emphasized are theideas that these programs are essentially
 income redistributional measures and that, given political forces, the
 programs are attempts to redistribute efficiently. Variables associated
 with the cost to producers of generating political pressure and the social
 cost (deadweight losses)of redistribution are both found to be empirically
 important.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
