Author-Name:    Ross, Stephen A
Title:   Arbitrage and Martingales with Taxation. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 371-93
Issue: 2
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  April 
Abstract:
  This paper extends the martingale analysis of no arbitrage pricing to
 worlds with taxation. The absence of arbitrage is shown to imply the
 existence of different shadow prices for income streams that are subject
 to differing tax treatments. For example , no arbitrage implies the
 existence of different martingale measures for capita l gains and for
 ordinary income when they are differentially taxed, andfor item s such as
 depreciation expenses that influence only after- tax cash flows. The
 analysis is applied to several topics in finance including the debt/equity
 decision, tax options, and the taxation of dividends and pensions.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
