Author-Name:    Mankiw, N Gregory
Title:   Government Purchases and Real Interest Rates. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 407-19
Issue: 2
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  April 
Abstract:
  This paper examines the dynamic impact of government purchases in a
 simple general equilibrium model with both durable and nondurable consumer
 goods as well as productive capital. The model generates perhaps
 surprising results. In particular, increases in government purchases are
 shown to cause reductions in real interest rates. The model thus provides
 a possible explanation for the observed behavior of real interest rates
 around wars.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
